cards.name: Against All Odds
cards.text:
Choose one or both -
• Exile target artifact or creature you control, then return it to the battlefield under its owner's control.
• Return target artifact or creature card with mana value 3 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.

cards.text:
Toxic 1 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get a poison counter.)
When Annex Sentry enters the battlefield, exile target artifact or creature an opponent controls with mana value 3 or less until Annex Sentry leaves the battlefield.
cards.flavor: There's never a need to change the watch, for the servants of Norn are sleepless.

cards.name: Apostle of Invasion
cards.text:
Flying
Corrupted - As long as an opponent has three or more poison counters, Apostle of Invasion has double strike.
cards.flavor: "Be not afraid of the holy chorus. Join in rapturous harmony."

cards.name: Basilica Shepherd
cards.text:
Flying
When Basilica Shepherd enters the battlefield, create two 1/1 colorless Phyrexian Mite artifact creature tokens with toxic 1 and "This creature can't block." (Players dealt combat damage by them also get a poison counter.)

cards.name: Bladed Ambassador
cards.text:
Bladed Ambassador enters the battlefield with an oil counter on it.
{1}, Remove an oil counter from Bladed Ambassador: Bladed Ambassador gains indestructible until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "Let those thanebound dissenters prattle about their dead god. I serve the Mother of Machines, and in her name I carve out their heresy."

cards.name: Charge of the Mites
cards.text:
Choose one-
• Charge of the Mites deals damage equal to the number of creatures you control to target creature or planeswalker.
• Create two 1/1 colorless Phyrexian Mite artifact creature tokens with toxic 1 and "This creature can't block." (Players dealt combat damage by them also get a poison counter.)

cards.text: Target creature you control gets +2/+2 until end of turn. If that creature has toxic, draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Elspeth, my friend, the Multiverse has answered my prayers to bring you here so that I may gather you into my pride and forever protect you."

cards.name: Crawling Chorus
cards.text:
Toxic 1 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get a poison counter.)
When Crawling Chorus dies, create a 1/1 colorless Phyrexian Mite artifact creature token with toxic 1 and "This creature can't block."
cards.flavor: "We need not be swift. We are inexorable."

cards.name: Duelist of Deep Faith
cards.text:
Toxic 1 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get a poison counter.)
As long as it's your turn, Duelist of Deep Faith has first strike.
cards.flavor: "There is no hate behind our blades. We kill out of love, and the desire to share Norn's blessings with all."

cards.text:
Vigilance
If a permanent entering the battlefield causes a triggered ability of a permanent you control to trigger, that ability triggers an additional time.

cards.text:
No more than one creature can attack The Eternal Wanderer each combat.
[+1]: Exile up to one target artifact or creature. Return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of that player's next end step.
[0]: Create a 2/2 white Samurai creature token with double strike.
[−4]: For each player, choose a creature that player controls. Each player sacrifices all creatures they control not chosen this way.

cards.name: Flensing Raptor
cards.text:
Flying

cards.name: Jawbone Duelist
cards.text:
Double strike
Toxic 1 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get a poison counter.)

Lifelink

cards.name: Orthodoxy Enforcer

Vigilance

Enchant basic land you control

Flying

cards.flavor:
"Behold your inevitable defeat."

cards.flavor:
"Witness the glory of true, unwavering unity."
-Ajani

cards.name: Resistance Reunited
cards.text:
Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
Equipped creatures you control gain indestructible until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "Well, aren't you a sight for sore eyes!" said Koth. "I was about to say the same, my friend," Elspeth replied.

cards.name: Sinew Dancer

{3}{W}, {T}: Tap target creature.
Corrupted - {W}, {T}: Tap target creature. Activate only if an opponent has three or more poison counters.

cards.name: Swooping Lookout
cards.text: Flying, vigilance
cards.flavor:
"It's hard to tell with this glare, but those must be the skyhunter reinforcements! They have arrived at last!"
-Prahan, Mirran rebel

This spell costs {3} more to cast if it targets a creature.
Exile target nonland permanent.

cards.name: Veil of Assimilation
cards.text: Whenever Veil of Assimilation or another artifact enters the battlefield under your control, target creature you control gets +1/+1 and gains vigilance until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"Hear only harmony. See only glory. Speak only truth."
-Atraxa

cards.flavor:
"Where once there was ignorance, Jin-Gitaxias brought knoweldge, and an age of progress dawned."
-Monument inscription

cards.name: Bring the Ending

Corrupted - Counter that spell instead if its controller has three or more poison counters.

cards.name: Chrome Prowler

Flash

cards.flavor: It can catch a rat and perform a spinal tap with one graceful swipe of its paw.

cards.name: Distorted Curiosity
cards.text:
Corrupted - This spell costs {2} less to cast if an opponent has three or more poison counters.
Draw two cards.
cards.flavor: "Free will was an illusion so perfect it fooled even me. I know better now."

cards.flavor:
"Careful-however they might look, they're not human. A step too close and they'll drag you in."
-Kara Vrist, resistance spymaster

Whenever another artifact enters the battlefield under your control, Eye of Malcator becomes a 4/4 Phyrexian Eye artifact creature until end of turn.

cards.name: Font of Progress
cards.text:
Font of Progress enters the battlefield with two oil counters on it.
{3}, {T}: Target player mills X cards, where X is the number of oil counters on Font of Progress.
cards.flavor:
"Drink deeply of the truth, and become compleat."
-Tamiyo

cards.flavor: An inconsistency in a routine vivisection sparked a revelation about the inner workings of the Orthodoxy's centurions.

Flying
